@startuml State Pattern Main Components

interface State {
    + handle(context: Context): void
}

class ConcreteStateA implements State {
    + handle(context: Context): void
}

class ConcreteStateB implements State {
    + handle(context: Context): void
}

class ConcreteStateC implements State {
    + handle(context: Context): void
}

class Context {
    - state: State
    + setState(state: State): void
    + request(): void
    + getState(): State
}

' Relationships
Context *-- State : manages
ConcreteStateA ..> Context : changes state
ConcreteStateB ..> Context : changes state
ConcreteStateC ..> Context : changes state

note right: Context delegates to current state
note right: State can change context's state
note right: Eliminates conditional logic

@enduml
